Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.44,0:00:09.40,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Kagami Yoshimizu Theater"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.27,0:00:05.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.88,0:00:06.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.88,0:00:07.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grr!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.52,0:00:09.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit screwing around and start!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.40,0:00:12.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The ambiguous 3cm?\NDoes that mean it's plushy? Wait!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.40,0:00:15.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The wrapping is a uniform, argh,\Nit's not an act, pooh{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.57,0:00:17.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Gotta do your best, gotta just do it{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.29,0:00:18.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's time to catch 'n' release, eek{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.91,0:00:20.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Between sweat (whoop)\NSweat (whoop){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.73,0:00:23.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Darlin', darlin', freeze! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.59,0:00:30.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kinda lethargic,\Nsomething's kinda comin' out{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.00,0:00:31.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I love you... Oh wait,\None of those was different{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.92,0:00:33.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Worrywarts, high metal bars {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.20,0:00:34.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tasty thoughts... And that's enough!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.93,0:00:36.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The heated body of that\Nflying you-know-who{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.72,0:00:38.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's what you call a normal girlie{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.43,0:00:39.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Am I the only one surprised? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.60,0:00:40.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Seconds on pork-bone broth ramen\Nwith wire-hard noodles{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.77,0:00:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Da da da da da {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.98,0:00:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Pom-poms cheer squad{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.77,0:00:51.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's get cherry pie {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.37,0:00:52.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Happy fun welcoming party {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.87,0:00:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Look up! Sensation{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.46,0:00:57.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yeah! Feeling of existence,\Ndot dot small planet{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.58,0:00:59.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Collided and it melted away,\Nin total awe{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.20,0:01:00.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Go all out to sing, shi-ranger!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.91,0:01:02.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Take it away! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.12,0:01:06.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I should be the one who'll be\Nlaughing in the end{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.49,0:01:13.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Because I have the sailor suit\N← This is my conclusion{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.51,0:01:15.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's only Monday! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.82,0:01:19.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Already in a bad mood? What to do?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.37,0:01:26.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I really prefer the summer outfits\N← kya! Wah! Good! (cute!) < 3{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.14,0:01:29.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Until we approach 3 pixels,\Nno hesitations please ★{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.39,0:01:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Do your best, be energetic {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.02,0:01:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My darlin', darlin' please! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.44,0:01:36.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Recital ♪15 -Symphony ♪9\ND minor, K .125"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.82,0:01:40.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miyuki-{\i1}san{\i0}, do you have something\Nto do at the end of the year?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.76,0:01:42.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Izumi-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.62,0:01:44.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a festival going on,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.04,0:01:46.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I was wondering if you wanted\Nto come with me, Miyuki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.16,0:01:49.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A festival at the end of the year?\NThat sounds like fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.87,0:01:52.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it's really fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.46,0:01:55.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it like the Snow Festival?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.23,0:01:57.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I will be going to visit\Nmy family in the country...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.76,0:02:02.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I seem to remember getting\Nan invitation like this last summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.92,0:02:04.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kagami-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.04,0:02:06.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Translating Konata's words,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.22,0:02:09.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you're wanted as someone to\Nhelp her buy stuff at Comiket.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.44,0:02:11.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I went last summer, I was\Nreally surprised by everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.52,0:02:15.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not lying. A festival is a festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.00,0:02:17.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Going all alone is tough,\Nand no fun at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.49,0:02:20.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Let's Go to the Festival"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.53,0:02:24.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Izumi residence.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.10,0:02:26.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Konata?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.65,0:02:28.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm writing my New Year's\Ncards right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.56,0:02:30.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but are you guys in mourning?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.33,0:02:32.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't received\Na decline notice yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.17,0:02:35.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We aren't.\NWhy are you asking all of a sudden?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.34,0:02:40.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, didn't you take some\Nbereavement leave this year?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.44,0:02:43.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.83,0:02:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah. But we're fine now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.17,0:02:48.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me you're using such\Ncomic-book methods to...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.77,0:02:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shiny happy...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.60,0:02:52.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're right in the middle of\Nour big clean-up right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.36,0:02:53.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.90,0:02:56.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'd hate to hold you for\Ntoo long, so I'll be going now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.48,0:02:56.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.99,0:02:58.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.00,0:02:58.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.72,0:03:08.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is it...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.43,0:03:11.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you have other\Ntedious stuff to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.79,0:03:13.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you really want to tidy up,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.52,0:03:15.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but when you decide you're\Ngoing to be cleaning and start,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.69,0:03:17.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it suddenly gets to be tedious...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.92,0:03:20.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Konata, take breaks\Nonly in moderation!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.28,0:03:29.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Comiket, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.14,0:03:30.39,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"First time attending"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.21,0:03:31.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear that it's a huge festival,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.21,0:03:33.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it really starts early in the morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.72,0:03:35.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm looking forward to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.27,0:03:36.52,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Second time"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.44,0:03:37.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody told you anything about it, did they?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.61,0:03:38.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel sorry for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.75,0:03:40.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, you'll get used to it in no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.78,0:03:40.03,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Regular attendee"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.94,0:03:44.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsukasa, I'll tell you now that\Nthis event will tire you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.22,0:03:45.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In all sorts of ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.44,0:03:46.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to be okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.41,0:03:48.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll do my best.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.84,0:03:50.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if she really understands...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.54,0:04:06.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People of that nature are starting\Nto increase in number now!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.19,0:04:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, the light will soon\Nturn green over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.32,0:04:22.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Sis, this place is rather scary...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.32,0:04:22.76,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,--Please make rows of \Nfive, and proceed slowly!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.25,0:04:23.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--That's why I told you so.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.35,0:04:28.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. I have to explain\Nyour share of the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.08,0:04:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our share?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.92,0:04:32.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, take these.\NThey're your shopping lists.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.91,0:04:35.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When we enter, first, we'll split up,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.79,0:04:38.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I want you to visit all the circles\Nin the order shown on the map.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.44,0:04:41.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kagami and Tsukasa, you take\Nareas 1 to 3 in East Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.15,0:04:43.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go around areas 4 to 6.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.48,0:04:46.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But be careful. If you don't walk\Nthe route written down in red ink,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.83,0:04:49.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you'll get separated by the lines\Nfor the circles along the walls,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.13,0:04:51.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and you might not be able to\Nmove at all from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.48,0:04:53.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially here and here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.08,0:04:54.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you get caught in the crowd\Nin these areas,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.86,0:04:57.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you'll lose more than thirty minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.16,0:05:00.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you have to\Ntake this so seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.17,0:05:01.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't sweat it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.79,0:05:03.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The circles marked in green are those
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.48,0:05:05.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that you can visit in the afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.63,0:05:07.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They usually stock up\Non tons of copies,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.92,0:05:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so the danger of them\Nselling out is very low.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.00,0:05:13.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the morning, concentrate only\Non the places marked in red.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.21,0:05:15.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S is for new stuff, K is for\Npreviously released stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.80,0:05:17.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you aren't sure, just buy\Neverything they're selling,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.52,0:05:19.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,regardless of whether\Nit's new or reprinted.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.67,0:05:21.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's your ammunition.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.21,0:05:24.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take this, because it's bad to fiddle\Nwith your wallet during checkout.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.17,0:05:26.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The café au lait is to\Nmaintain your sugar levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.35,0:05:27.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drink some every thirty minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.95,0:05:32.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll meet up again at the end\Nright here, at exactly 13:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.77,0:05:35.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll wait fifteen minutes for you,\Nbut if you don't show up,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.39,0:05:37.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go look in the infirmary\Nfor you, so be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.40,0:05:38.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That will be all. Questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.94,0:05:41.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These are the only times\Nthat you really show
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.64,0:05:44.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,an amazing amount of\Nintellect and passion...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.35,0:05:46.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't run!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.82,0:05:48.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Climax from the get-go!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.52,0:05:52.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're currently limiting sales of\Nthe new issue to four per person!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.79,0:05:54.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We ask for your cooperation!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.89,0:06:00.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, excuse me... This is A-92, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.35,0:06:01.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.32,0:06:04.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you want one copy of each\Nnew issue? That will be 1000 yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.65,0:06:05.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, and?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.50,0:06:08.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, which ones are your new issues?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.68,0:06:10.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, the new issues are\Nthis one and this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.89,0:06:12.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're both 500 yen each.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.16,0:06:13.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, thanks for the hard work!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.72,0:06:16.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Were the sweets I brought in tasty?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.75,0:06:17.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so glad!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.92,0:06:20.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, can I have three of each?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.12,0:06:21.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Thanks a lot!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.48,0:06:24.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Slippery Brigade Leader and\NNaughty Captain, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.30,0:06:26.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That will be 3000 yen!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.71,0:06:29.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll just have these.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.96,0:06:32.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, that's 4500 yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.09,0:06:32.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.73,0:06:34.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.75,0:06:45.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tango down. Proceeding\Nto the next point.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.63,0:06:48.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, this is East Hall?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.08,0:06:51.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And north should be\Nthis way, so let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.74,0:06:53.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wah... Wait a minute...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.47,0:06:56.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me... I want to go that way!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.36,0:07:01.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've basically covered\Nall of the big ones...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.24,0:07:03.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see, the next circle to go to...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.57,0:07:06.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Spellbound ~captured~"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.55,0:07:18.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a little bit...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.11,0:07:23.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gauron doing so much to Sousuke...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.56,0:07:26.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is so...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.75,0:07:27.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.26,0:07:30.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's 500 yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.17,0:07:31.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.93,0:07:33.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too stimulating for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.72,0:07:40.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's here! It's her!\NIt's Legendary Girl A!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.09,0:07:41.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.18,0:07:43.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're freaking out,\Nshe'll think something is up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.26,0:07:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but the places\Nshe buys stuff from...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.17,0:07:50.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The strange jinx, where most of them\Nsuddenly grow into popular circles!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.19,0:07:52.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible to ask me\Nnot to be excited about her!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.40,0:07:53.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.29,0:07:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we put so much effort\Ninto putting this issue together!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.90,0:07:57.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just for her to buy one!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.45,0:08:00.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right... It's the end of the year,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.43,0:08:02.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,yet we took time off work\Nto do our best.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.91,0:08:04.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This year... We'll make sure\Nthat this year...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.59,0:08:05.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I look?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.64,0:08:07.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, go right ahead!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.91,0:08:19.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.96,0:08:23.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We put lots of effort in drawing\Nthat scene involving the live show.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.95,0:08:26.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm... Needs some work.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.77,0:08:28.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks a lot!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.63,0:08:34.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't cry... We'll make sure\Nthat next summer...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.96,0:08:38.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.01,0:08:39.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.66,0:08:43.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know where I can find Pu-61?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.53,0:08:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pu? Wasn't the Pu section\Nin East Hall?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.52,0:08:48.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is East Hall?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.42,0:08:50.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is West Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.12,0:08:51.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to go to East Hall,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.44,0:08:54.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you need to line up over there,\Nand go upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.43,0:08:57.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know how long that will take?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.08,0:09:00.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see... This time of day,\Nit should take about an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.56,0:09:05.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Network Busy"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.23,0:09:06.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, that's all!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.77,0:09:10.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Kona-{\i1}chan{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.92,0:09:14.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just got back, finally, from\Nthis place called West Hall...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.82,0:09:19.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this event, you totally get lost if\Nyou get washed away by the crowds...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.82,0:09:22.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I was in line to go to the\Nbathroom for an entire hour...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.84,0:09:25.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I was thinking the\Nshopping menu I gave you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.18,0:09:27.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was too strenuous for\Na first-time attendee, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.12,0:09:30.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can take it easy and look around\Ntogether in the afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.35,0:09:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's planning on seeing even more?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.00,0:09:37.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's gotten much easier since they\Nstarted holding it here in Ariake.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.60,0:09:39.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Back when they held it in Harumi Hall,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.39,0:09:42.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there were only two\Nconvenience stores in the area.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.19,0:09:43.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Harumi Hall?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.42,0:09:48.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think the last one in Harumi Hall\Nwas about twelve years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.22,0:09:50.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait. How old were you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.62,0:09:54.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About five years old?\NDad took me there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.19,0:09:57.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We always spent two nights in\Nthis place called Hotel Urashima.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.74,0:09:59.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My first time was a Summer Comiket,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.95,0:10:03.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but back in those days, the second\Nfloor of the New Hall was amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.02,0:10:06.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The huge amount of sweat from\Nthe attendees turned into steam,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.09,0:10:08.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and a cloud fluffed up\Nin the air above them...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.96,0:10:10.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough.\NI don't want to hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.75,0:10:13.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's more convenient in a lot of ways,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.45,0:10:15.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,now that they're holding it in Ariake.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.24,0:10:17.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, maybe because the event\Nhas gotten so big,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.42,0:10:21.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the young attendees nowadays think\Nlike they're customers or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.34,0:10:23.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It makes me so sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.01,0:10:26.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the beginning, it was an event\Nthat everyone made together.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.24,0:10:28.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to interrupt when\Nyou're reminiscing so much,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.73,0:10:29.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I don't get it at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.15,0:10:34.15,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,"Akira Kogami at Comic Market" \N"Apology: Due to sudden illness, \Nwill not be attending today."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.40,0:10:38.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a place like this too?\NWe didn't come here in the summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.96,0:10:42.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Though I think all\Nthe good stuff is all sold out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.32,0:10:43.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.36,0:10:45.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's Nagato, Nagato!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.33,0:10:48.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--The person behind \NNaga-mon is selling stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.76,0:10:48.56,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,--Thank you so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.08,0:10:49.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--So who is she, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.56,0:10:50.16,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,--It's a pleasure to meet \Nyou. Please do your best!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.32,0:10:51.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--What do you mean, the Haruhi \Ngoods are all sold out?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.95,0:10:54.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Without those Nagato cards, there\Nwas no point coming out here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.88,0:10:56.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Wow, that's the worst...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.88,0:10:57.64,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,--Please calm down. You'll cause \Ntrouble to our other customers...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.88,0:10:58.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Like I was saying earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.64,0:10:58.46,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,--Like I care!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.46,0:11:00.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--There are more and more \Npeople like that lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.46,0:11:00.63,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,--This is past the level of selling stuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.63,0:11:03.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm terribly sorry\Nto inform our customers!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.63,0:11:07.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, our limited-edition\Ngoods have already sold out!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.28,0:11:09.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.44,0:11:10.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.38,0:11:12.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, coming by this late...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.32,0:11:12.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.89,0:11:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but you have to\Nline up in the morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.44,0:11:17.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.96,0:11:19.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Asia...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.53,0:11:21.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.66,0:11:25.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doing your best to please\Nthe customers that missed out!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.56,0:11:27.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you've forgotten\Nthat spirit, then what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.64,0:11:31.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, we're down to\Nthe leftover items here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.32,0:11:35.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you say "leftover items"?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.09,0:11:39.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good things come to those who wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.07,0:11:44.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unaffected by the fad shows\Nand cheap {\i1}moe{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.84,0:11:48.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Comiket is the prime opportunity\Nto see something at its true value!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.49,0:11:51.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, after all the\Nlimited-edition goods are gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.47,0:11:55.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is when the real battle begins for\Nthe corporate booths, is it not?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.15,0:11:58.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it, dude...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.15,0:12:00.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then suggest something\Nto this customer here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.92,0:12:03.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The finest hidden gem\Nthat you can think of!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.42,0:12:06.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something... Isn't there\Na weapon somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.37,0:12:10.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.75,0:12:13.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! This one over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.04,0:12:16.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Nagato sells so well,\Nbut this is, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.65,0:12:18.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even Koizumi sells well...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.41,0:12:21.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up! This was left over\Nfrom three years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.08,0:12:23.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ones for the captain\Nsold out on the first day, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.05,0:12:25.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so, how about this Kyon here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.05,0:12:27.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I recommend Sousuke!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.08,0:12:28.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was looking for the\NCoco Saikoubi card...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.93,0:12:32.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You idiots!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.64,0:12:36.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.83,0:12:37.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Takahashi,\Nthe company president!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.98,0:12:40.40,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Company"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.24,0:12:41.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! I am the company \Npresident, Takahashi!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.40,0:12:41.65,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"President"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.65,0:12:44.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard all you had to say!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.66,0:12:48.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--It's fine that you want to show our\Ncustomers a new sense of value!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.36,0:12:47.79,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,--That place is always hyper.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.79,0:12:49.42,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,--Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.40,0:12:51.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--However, trying to push unpopular \Ncharacters onto them...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.42,0:12:51.21,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,--R-Really...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.82,0:12:54.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't abide such\Nmean-spirited behavior!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.12,0:12:56.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, both of them are\Nmain characters...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.28,0:12:58.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Lucky Star{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.33,0:13:11.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis, I'm sleepy...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.68,0:13:13.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sleepy too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.23,0:13:17.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Helping the family out right after\Ncoming back from Ariake...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.42,0:13:20.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can they have an event\Nlike that right on New Year's Eve?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.18,0:13:24.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kagami, Tsukasa, Happy New Year!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.61,0:13:27.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kona-{\i1}chan{\i0}, Happy New Year!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.20,0:13:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're full of spirit, as busy\Nas it was this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.70,0:13:32.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As cold as it is, I thought\Nyou might not bother coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.99,0:13:34.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you have a point...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.92,0:13:37.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But since the sum of the year\Nrests on New Year's Day,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.44,0:13:41.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that first shrine visit helps you\Ngather strength for the coming year.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.24,0:13:42.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's admirable of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.67,0:13:44.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's what Dad said.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.12,0:13:44.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.81,0:13:46.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suddenly have a weird feeling...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.65,0:13:48.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The shrine maiden outfit\Nis a nice change!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.43,0:13:49.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yup, yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.39,0:13:52.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stuff like this, stuff like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.38,0:13:54.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm done praying.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.27,0:13:55.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.76,0:13:58.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsukasa, did you guys\Npray and stuff already?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.62,0:14:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, Sis,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.00,0:14:02.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,weren't you feverishly praying\Nfor something earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.28,0:14:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You id--You don't need\Nto mention those things!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.80,0:14:06.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't that feverish about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.88,0:14:08.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just thought that\Nit would be nice if this year,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.72,0:14:12.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could be in the same class as\Nyou and Miyuki for once, Tsukasa.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.35,0:14:13.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.96,0:14:15.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis, what about Kona-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.87,0:14:18.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kagami, you actually\Nhave a pretty cute side.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.99,0:14:19.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.95,0:14:22.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't say anything because\NI knew you'd tease me that way!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.51,0:14:24.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That resistance is just so...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.60,0:14:25.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.51,0:14:29.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis, you've always been the\Nonly one in a different class...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.20,0:14:32.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if Miss Kuroi\Ndoesn't like me...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.55,0:14:37.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll pray so that I can be in\Nthe same class as you too, Sis.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.42,0:14:38.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsukasa!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.31,0:14:42.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, Kagami needs to be\Nin a different class as us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.04,0:14:43.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.34,0:14:46.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, we can borrow stuff\Nwhen we forget,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.62,0:14:48.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and we won't get caught\Neven if we copy her homework,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.84,0:14:52.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and with Kagami in the class,\Nmy score ranking will drop!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.04,0:14:53.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you can be all alone\Nin a different class.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.25,0:14:55.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.10,0:14:56.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The other day, Sebastian...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.32,0:14:59.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Schoolgirls are so great...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.96,0:15:03.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like to buy\Nfortunes again this year?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.74,0:15:05.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good idea, since we're out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.84,0:15:07.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Unlucky" "Great blessings"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.52,0:15:10.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looking good from the beginning\Nof the new year.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.24,0:15:12.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really! I saw something\Nreally nice too!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.75,0:15:14.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This year is looking to be a great year!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.93,0:15:16.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.64,0:15:18.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's the worst right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.01,0:15:20.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the only way for your\Nfortunes to go is up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.65,0:15:21.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure good things will happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.90,0:15:25.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. How to put it... I guess\Nit's all in how you say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.55,0:15:26.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.57,0:15:30.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's the case, why don't you\Ntie it to a branch to lift the curse?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.16,0:15:31.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I'll do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.20,0:15:33.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, tons of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.74,0:15:35.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, over here too!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.32,0:15:37.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.83,0:15:44.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this what you call being unlucky?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.40,0:15:45.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think so...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.29,0:15:47.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whether or not good things happen,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.16,0:15:49.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in the end, all depends on yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.39,0:15:51.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A fortune is nothing more\Nthan a test of luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.69,0:15:54.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That may be true...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.14,0:15:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's not something someone\Ninvolved in selling them should say.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.30,0:15:59.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Might as well try to\Nget all the fortunes
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.08,0:16:01.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from "Great Blessings" down to\N"Terribly Unlucky"...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.55,0:16:03.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are they trading cards?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.40,0:16:05.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe there are secret ones too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.95,0:16:09.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Secret paper fortunes?!\NWhat kind of fortune would that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.23,0:16:10.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like "Ultra Super Unlucky"\Nor something.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.97,0:16:12.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, an even worse one?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.59,0:16:13.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want one of those!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.79,0:16:16.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's something where, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.19,0:16:18.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,collecting them all\Ngets you a special item.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.32,0:16:19.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, there's nothing like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.74,0:16:21.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, I was thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.20,0:16:24.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as I was staring at that\Ngiant "kagami" mochi...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.08,0:16:25.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like, this big.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.86,0:16:28.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kagami, is your name\Nderived from that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.98,0:16:30.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's not totally wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.96,0:16:34.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A "kagami" mochi is round,\Nlike an old-fashioned mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.54,0:16:38.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Long ago, mirrors were said\Nto harbor deities.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.44,0:16:42.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So they named me in hopes that I'd\Nhave the blessings of such deities.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.38,0:16:46.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, the roundness is said to mean\Na happy, well-rounded family.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.35,0:16:49.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The roots of the name are so mystical,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.16,0:16:52.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,yet the actual person ended up\Ngrowing up to be such a realist!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.37,0:16:59.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like one?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.95,0:17:04.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there sure are a lot\Nof worshippers here!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.48,0:17:06.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it is the New Year.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.43,0:17:08.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this is nothing compared\Nto all the famous places.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.32,0:17:13.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder, of all these people,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.85,0:17:16.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,how many are like my Dad and\Nhere for the shrine maidens?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.86,0:17:18.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that how you think?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.12,0:17:20.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Most of them aren't like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.77,0:17:21.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.03,0:17:35.65,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,"January 1, 2007 (Mon)" "Happy New Year"\N"Flight to the Future" \N"First Sunrise at Mount Fuji"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.95,0:17:40.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once again, I bid you\Na happy New Year,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.67,0:17:44.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--and my best regards for this upcoming year.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.21,0:17:44.16,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,--Now, as usual, we'll \Ncall out for Do Ooshiba.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.44,0:17:45.40,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,--Mr. Do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.44,0:17:45.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Yes. Best regards.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.40,0:17:50.48,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,--Yes! Happy New Year! I'm Do!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.48,0:17:52.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now look at this {\i1}beautiful {\i0}scenery!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.70,0:17:55.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's so {\i1}great{\i0}! It's so {\i1}fantastic{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.61,0:17:57.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now look here, such\Na {\i1}pretty flower{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.60,0:18:00.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Many many {\i0}are blooming here...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.25,0:18:05.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, want some tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.53,0:18:07.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'll have some!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.30,0:18:12.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.04,0:18:13.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.20,0:18:21.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, you want to play games?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.03,0:18:23.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, you want rice cake soup?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.03,0:18:24.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.29,0:18:25.79,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"New Year's Allowance"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.68,0:18:25.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.79,0:18:29.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess he was happy with\Nhow I kept fussing over him
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.07,0:18:31.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,until I got my New Year's allowance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.55,0:18:32.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm exhausted!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.46,0:18:37.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you know...\NYou guys really get along well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.13,0:18:39.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And, now that I've safely gotten\Nmy New Year's allowance,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.98,0:18:42.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'll head out\Nto Gamers right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.54,0:18:43.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.47,0:18:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's really a pain that there's\Nno stores like that in the suburbs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.52,0:18:49.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're really strapped for cash\Nin the first place,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.42,0:18:51.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and taking the train costs money.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.13,0:18:53.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish there was a store\Nlike that in our area.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.55,0:18:57.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But all sorts of shops are catering\Nto online shopping nowadays.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.64,0:19:00.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So don't those places have it as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.16,0:19:02.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.11,0:19:05.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, you can get the points\Njust fine through online shopping,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.50,0:19:07.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but what's fun is actually\Ngoing to the stores yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.87,0:19:10.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and looking around to see if you\Ncan make an unexpected find...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.65,0:19:13.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's up with that?! You're\Ntotally set on using your money!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.25,0:19:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And now, the daikon radish\Nwill soon become transparent...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.40,0:19:19.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are these bags called\Nmeager (pochi) bags?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.15,0:19:21.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That comes from a meager\Namount (pochitto),
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.32,0:19:22.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or just this much (koreppocchi),
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.51,0:19:24.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it apparently means\Na bag to put loose change in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.81,0:19:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.71,0:19:27.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe "pochitto"\Nwas in western Japan,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.50,0:19:29.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And "koreppocchi" was\Nhow you say it in eastern Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.97,0:19:39.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Happy New Year! This is Takara.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.45,0:19:41.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Miyuki-{\i1}san{\i0}? Happy New Year!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.82,0:19:46.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And anyway, I wanted to hear about\Nthe etymology of "meager bags"...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.40,0:19:49.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Meager bags? If I recall correctly...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.40,0:19:50.44,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,--Konata... You can trust \Nyour father every so often...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.04,0:19:51.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--It comes from "pochitto" or "koreppocchi",
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.44,0:19:53.79,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,--At the least, ask around \Nwhere I can't see you...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.47,0:19:53.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--and apparently it means a \Nbag to put loose change in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.89,0:19:57.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, I guess I'll say my\NNew Year's greetings
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.84,0:20:00.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to all of my gaming friends too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.09,0:20:03.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Yamanka : (T_T)"\N"Gatongo: don't cry!"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.72,0:20:03.43,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Friend Konakona has logged in."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.43,0:20:04.43,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Gatongo: oh?"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.43,0:20:05.43,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Konakona: happy new year!"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.43,0:20:06.43,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Yamanka: oh! Happy\Nnew year! (>w<)b"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.43,0:20:07.43,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Gatongo: happy (rotf1)"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.43,0:20:10.93,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Konakona: I'm finally able to log in!\NThe end of the year was so busy..."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.93,0:20:13.60,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Friend Nanakon has logged in."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.89,0:20:14.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's my teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.65,0:20:17.69,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Konakona: Ma'am, Happy New Year."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.69,0:20:18.94,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Nanakon: Yo! Happy\NNew Year! (^w^)/~"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.94,0:20:21.19,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Konakona: My best regards\Nfor the upcoming year."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.19,0:20:25.16,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Nanakon: yup yup, best regards\Nfor this coming year! (>w<)b"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.16,0:20:28.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All in all, she's always online.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.01,0:20:30.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't she have anything else to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.38,0:20:32.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No wonder she doesn't\Nhave a boyfriend.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.33,0:20:34.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Lucky Star{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.74,0:20:38.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Lucky Channel{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.67,0:20:41.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Morning Luckies!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.96,0:20:44.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Minoru Shiraishi,\Nassistant to Akira-{\i1}sama{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.64,0:20:47.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Times pass by so quickly, and {\i1}Lucky Channel\N{\i0}is already on episode twelve.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.52,0:20:51.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This ocean is hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.54,0:20:55.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, um, as you can see,\NAkira-{\i1}sama {\i0}was slated to appear
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.84,0:20:58.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in the main segment\Nas well as this episode,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.17,0:21:00.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but her health deteriorated\Nright before the filming...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.88,0:21:01.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.32,0:21:07.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, you have a cold, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.16,0:21:10.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we left a life-size signboard\Nof you in its place, Akira-{\i1}sama{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.62,0:21:12.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so if they all watched carefully,\NI'm sure they...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.68,0:21:18.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes? Wait, Akira-{\i1}sama{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.07,0:21:23.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, as seen here, it seems that\NAkira-{\i1}sama {\i0}is very tired this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.64,0:21:25.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I'd like to end it right about here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.64,0:21:28.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, everyone, bye-nee!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.59,0:21:30.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Don't get so conceited"?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.89,0:21:32.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I'm not!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.67,0:21:36.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Me?\N"You'll hear the true version
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.38,0:21:38.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of {\i1}Take it! The Sailor Suit{\i0},\Nso look forward to it"?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.92,0:21:40.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"If you don't watch the next episode,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.33,0:21:42.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll lecture you in\Nthe name of Mars"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.14,0:21:42.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Fumoff{\i0}--
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.09,0:21:48.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was pretty lively.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.92,0:21:50.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.24,0:21:51.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.32,0:21:52.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody's entered a song.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.62,0:21:54.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Considering the order,\Nyou would be up next, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.44,0:21:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is when you need\Nto have a song in!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.38,0:21:58.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hadn't decided!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.85,0:22:01.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What song should I pick?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.15,0:22:02.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I'll look for one too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.60,0:22:04.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, there's a menu here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.64,0:22:05.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.34,0:22:07.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can eat here as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.50,0:22:08.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.19,0:22:11.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sang that song a while ago,\Nso the flow isn't good.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.56,0:22:13.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I should have saved it for later.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.50,0:22:14.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, flow?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.88,0:22:17.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How to put it...\NYou know how there is one?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.20,0:22:19.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How to get yourself wound up\Nto sing a song and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.69,0:22:20.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.83,0:22:22.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I sing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.75,0:22:32.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They have tambourines here as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.22,0:22:34.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You use these to liven the place up.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.47,0:22:37.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Yuki-{\i1}chan{\i0}, let's try using these, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.12,0:22:38.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds great.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.17,0:22:39.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, this song!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.58,0:22:42.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care if it's a hardcore\Nanime song, just put something in!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.14,0:22:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I put in a song that would\Ngenerally liven up the audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.27,0:22:48.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.30,0:22:49.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know this song, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.85,0:22:50.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.80,0:22:52.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.80,0:22:56.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I made a mistake.\NLet's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.41,0:23:16.91,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Next Episode Preview"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.92,0:23:16.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, what's with the\Nnext episode of {\i1}Lucky Star{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.97,0:23:17.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miyuki here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.20,0:23:20.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When describing something\Ngoing at the top of the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.20,0:23:22.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,putting every opponent far behind,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.46,0:23:25.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there are times that the term\N"no contest" (dantotsu) is used.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.80,0:23:27.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is said that this is\Nactually an abbreviation of
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.63,0:23:28.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"by far the top of the line"\N(danzen TOP).
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.21,0:23:33.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The first person to use this term\Nwithin written text was apparently,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.55,0:23:35.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,literally, the man who\Nwon the election
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.44,0:23:38.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for the governor of Tokyo\Nwith a "no contest."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.92,0:23:40.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode: Delicious Day.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.10,0:23:43.44,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Delicious Day"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.98,0:23:42.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please look forward to it!
